1 10. Beginning July 1, 2029, a minimum of fourteen and one-half
2 percent (14.5%) of the actual paid base salary of each member of the
3 System employed by the municipality;
4 11. Beginning July 1, 2030, a minimum of fourteen and three-
5 quarters percent (14.75%) of the actual paid base salary of each
6 member of the System employed by the municipality; and
7 12. Beginning July 1, 2031, a minimum of fifteen percent (15%)
8 of the actual paid base salary of each member of the System employed
9 by the municipality.
10 The sum appropriated shall be paid online to the System within
11 ten (10) days following the payroll period on which the contribution
12 is based.
13 The state shall make such appropriation as is necessary to
14 assure the retirement benefits provided by the this article.
15 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
16 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
17 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
18 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
19 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
